-- America Movil net profit jumps 52 pct
-- 
-- Wed Apr 25, 2007 5:24pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/25/us-americamovil-results-idUSN2529038120070425

 

 MEXICO CITY  (Reuters) - America Movil, the largest cellphone operator in Latin America, posted a much better than expected 52 percent rise in first-quarter net profit as it boosted its subscribers to 131.2 million. 

 Mexico-based America Movil, controlled by tycoon Carlos Slim, said on Wednesday its January-March net profit was 15.797 billion pesos ($1.43 billion), up from 10.362 billion pesos a year ago. Revenue for America Movil ( AMX.N ) ( AMXL.MX ) rose 28 percent, also slightly better than analyst forecasts, to 67.7 billion pesos. ($1 = 11.044 pesos at end March)